Internal Control Specialist - PT General Motors Indonesia Manufacturing
Internal Control Specialist  -
Internal Control Specialist
Responsibilities
Assist with the ongoing SOX 404 program, including but not limited to: control documentation, internal control testing, change management, and remediation plans.Perform various financial, operational and compliance audits, risk assessments or related projects with oversight.Assist with identification and oversight of significant financial, operational and compliance risks across the enterprise.Assist with coordination for external financial and SOX audits.Gain understanding of the Company’s products and relevant processes in order to assist with identification of risk or compliance concerns and/or to evaluate controls.Perform various other duties or special projects as requested based on department objectivesPerform NST (New SOX Tool), and other risk management instruments to maintain a strong process for reviewing internal controls, identifying weaknesses, and driving corrective actions.Prepare and maintain reports on internal control review results and corrective actions requiredProvide reports to GM Audit Services as required on local risk management reviewsIdentify and implement best practiceProvide consultative servicesAnalyze risk and assist in identification of root causePromote common practices (local & corporate)Provide training to employees on correct practicesHeighten internal control awareness Requirement: Bachelors degree in Accounting3+ years accounting or auditing experience, including SOX and internal controls compliance, with strong preference to experience working for Big 4 Audit firmsUnderstanding of COSO frameworkStrong PSAK Accounting standards knowledge; exposure to US GAAP a plusExcellent communication and presentation skillsSelf-starter, motivatedManagerial courage
